            <h1>Brown Butter Chocolate Chip Cookies</h1>
<img src="https://easygayoven.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/chocolate-chip-cookies-20221532-819x1024.jpg" style="float:right;height:500px" />

<h2>ingredients:</h2>
<h3>
    - 2 1/4 cups flour (293 grams)
    <br />
    - 3/4 teaspoon baking soda
    <br />
    - 1/4 teaspoon baking powder
    <br />
    - 1 teaspoon salt
    <br />
    - 1/2 cup sugar (100 grams)
    <br />
    - 1 cup dark brown sugar, lightly packed (190 grams)
    <br />
    - 14 tablespoons unsalted butter (197 grams)+ 2 tablespoons water
    <br />
    - 1 egg + 1 egg yolk
    <br />
    - 2 teaspoons of vanilla
    <br />
    - 200g chopped chocolate bars
    <br />
    - Optional: 1/2 tsp coffee powder
</h3>

<h2>Instructions:</h2>
<h3>
    1. Brown butter: cook butter on the stovetop on medium heat while stirring until butter becomes brown. this should take around 8 minutes.
    <br />
    2. Let butter cool and add the water to the butter.
    <br />
    3. Whisk butter with sugar and brown sugar until combined.
    <br />
    4. Add egg, egg yolk and vanilla and whisk until batter lightens.
    <br />
    5. Fold in the dry ingredients.
    <br />
    6. Add the chopped chocolate.
    <br />
    7. Make into balls and referigerate for 2 hours.
    <br />
    8. Bake on 180 Celsius for 10 minutes
    <br />
    9. Let rest for 5+ min before removing from pan
</h3>
</asp:Content>
